  <sect2 id="file-format-troff">
  <title><command>TROFF</command> Format</title>
  <para>This format is supported by the <quote>HTML &amp; TeX</quote> plug-in.</para>
  <note><para>This format is only available when saving files.</para></note>
  <para>Files in this format are useful because they can be converted with the 
  <command>groff</command> or <command>troff</command> commands 
  into various other common formats. For example, given a <command>TROFF</command> file 
  <replaceable>myfile.me</replaceable>, the command</para>
  <screen>
  groff -me -t -Tps <replaceable>myfile.me</replaceable> ><replaceable>myfile.ps</replaceable>
  </screen>
  <para>will create a postscript file of the corresponding table.</para>
  <para>Similarly, the command</para>
  <screen>
groff -me -t -Tascii <replaceable>myfile.me</replaceable> ><replaceable>myfile.ascii</replaceable>
  </screen>
  <para>creates an <keycap>ascii</keycap> (straight text) file.</para>
  <example>
  <title>Creating an <keycap>ASCII</keycap> File</title>
  <para>If we save <xref linkend="file-format-dvi-ex1"> as a <command>troff</command> file 
  <replaceable>hypothetical-sales.me</replaceable> and then execute the command</para>
  <screen>
groff -me -t -Tascii <replaceable>hypothetical-sales.me</replaceable> ><replaceable>hypothetical-sales.ascii</replaceable>
  </screen>
